(118, 'Dieffenbachia (Dumb Cane)', '299', '199', 98, 'product-featured-118.jpg', '<p>Dieffenbachia, commonly known as Dumb Cane, is a popular tropical houseplant admired for its large,</p><p>&nbsp;lush, and often variegated leaves. The plant gets its nickname because its sap contains toxins that</p><p>&nbsp;can cause temporary speechlessness (hence \"dumb\") if ingested. Native to Central and South America,</p><p>&nbsp;Dieffenbachia is loved for its easy care, air-purifying qualities, and bold decorative presence.</p>', '<p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" data-filename=\"base64.jpg\" style=\"width: 449px;\"><br></p>', 131, 1, 1, 5);
