(119, 'Monstera Deliciosa (Swiss Cheese Plant)', '200', '149', 97, 'product-featured-119.jpg', '<p>Monstera deliciosa, often called the Swiss Cheese Plant, is a tropical climbing plant famous for its large,</p><p>Â glossy, heart-shaped leaves with dramatic splits and holes (called fenestrations). Native to the</p><p>Â rainforests of Central America, itâ€™s a favorite among houseplant enthusiasts for its bold look and</p><p>Â relatively easy care. The name \"deliciosa\" comes from its rare edible fruit, known for its sweet,Â </p><p>tropical flavor â€” though indoor plants almost never fruit.</p>', '<p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" data-filename=\"base64_2.jpg\" style=\"width: 449px;\"><br></p>', 18, 1, 1, 5);
