(121, 'snake plant (sansevieria)', '199', '149', 99, 'product-featured-121.jpg', '<p>The Snake Plant, also known by its older botanical name Sansevieria (now often reclassified under Dracaena),</p><p>&nbsp;is a hardy, low-maintenance houseplant celebrated for its upright, sword-like leaves and its air-purifying&nbsp;</p><p>abilities. Sometimes called Mother-in-Law\'s Tongue due to its sharp, pointed leaves, the plant is native to&nbsp;</p><p>tropical regions of West Africa. It thrives on neglect, making it perfect for beginners or busy plant owners.</p>', '<p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" data-filename=\"base64_4.jpg\" style=\"width: 449px;\"><br></p>', 9, 1, 1, 5);
