(123, 'Kalachuchi (Desert Rose)', '249', '179', 97, 'product-featured-123.jpg', '<p>Kalachuchi, more widely known as the Desert Rose (Adenium obesum), is a stunning flowering plant native to Africa</p><p>&nbsp;and the Arabian Peninsula. Itâ€™s famous for its swollen, thick trunk (called a caudex), vibrant trumpet-shaped&nbsp;</p><p>flowers, and succulent-like properties. In the Philippines and other tropical countries, Kalachuchi is a beloved&nbsp;</p><p>ornamental plant often associated with cemeteries and gardens. Despite its delicate beauty, it\'s extremely tough&nbsp;</p><p>and drought-resistant.</p>', '<p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" data-filename=\"base64_6.jpg\" style=\"width: 449px;\"><br></p>', 20, 1, 1, 6);
