(125, 'Ti Plant (Cordyline fruticosa)', '249', '199', 50, 'product-featured-125.jpg', '<p>The Ti Plant (Cordyline fruticosa), sometimes called the Good Luck Plant or Hawaiian Ti, is a colorful&nbsp;</p><p>tropical plant celebrated for its bold, glossy, and vibrant foliage. Native to Southeast Asia, Papua New Guinea,</p><p>&nbsp;and parts of Polynesia, the Ti Plant is deeply tied to cultural traditions, especially in Hawaii and&nbsp;</p><p>other Pacific islands, where itâ€™s seen as a symbol of protection, luck, and spiritual energy.</p>', '<p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" data-filename=\"base64_9\" style=\"width: 449px;\"><br></p>', 4, 1, 1, 6);
